# PropFrame Video Worker — Environment Variables

Copy this to `.env.local` in the project root for development.

```env
# ─── Database ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/propframe

# ─── Cloudflare R2 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
R2_ACCOUNT_ID=your-account-id
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key-id
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-access-key
R2_BUCKET=propframe-media
R2_PUBLIC_URL=https://your-public-url.r2.dev

# ─── Runway Gen-3 (AI Video Generation) ──────────────────────────────────────
RUNWAY_API_KEY=your-runway-api-key

# ─── Redis (BullMQ Job Queue) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# ─── Worker Settings ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
WORKER_CONCURRENCY=2
WORKER_RATE_LIMIT=10
```

## Running Locally

```bash
# Terminal 1 — Start Redis
docker run -d -p 6379:6379 redis:7-alpine

# Terminal 2 — Start the video worker
cd workers/video-render
npm install
npm run dev
```

## Runway Gen-3 Model

The worker uses Runway Gen-3 (gen3a_turbo) for image-to-video generation.
Gen-3 outputs 1280x720 — significantly better than CogVideoX's 480p.
Set `RUNWAY_API_KEY` in your `.env.local` to your Runway API key.
Cost: ~$0.50-2.00 per clip.

## Production Deployment

```bash
cd workers/video-render
npm run build
npm start
```

For production, deploy the worker as a separate service on a GPU machine.
